    <section id="about-section" class="content-section-efg123">
        <h2 class="section-title-hij456">Welcome to Tony's Family</h2>
        <div class="about-grid-klm789">
            <div class="about-text-nop012">
                <p>At Tony's Authentic Pizzeria, we believe that great pizza starts with passion, tradition, and the finest ingredients. Our family has been serving the community for over three decades, bringing the authentic taste of Italy to your neighborhood.</p>
                
                <p>Every pizza is hand-stretched using our secret dough recipe, topped with San Marzano tomatoes, fresh mozzarella, and ingredients sourced from local farms and trusted Italian suppliers. We take pride in maintaining the old-world techniques while embracing the warmth of modern hospitality.</p>
                
                <p>Whether you're joining us for a casual family dinner, celebrating a special occasion, or simply craving that perfect slice, our team treats every guest like family. <a href="#specialties-section" class="continue-link-fgh678">Click here to continue</a> exploring what makes our pizzeria special.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="about-image-qrs345">
                <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/1566837/pexels-photo-1566837.jpeg" alt="Traditional pizza making process">
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="history-section" class="content-section-efg123">
        <h2 class="section-title-hij456">Our Rich Heritage</h2>
        <div class="history-timeline-tuv678">
            <div class="timeline-item-wxy901">
                <div class="timeline-year-zab234">1987</div>
                <div class="timeline-content-cde567">
                    <h3>The Beginning</h3>
                    <p>Tony Marcelli immigrated from Naples, Italy, with nothing but his grandmother's pizza recipes and a dream to share authentic Italian flavors with his new community. He opened the first Tony's Pizzeria in a small storefront with just four tables and a wood-fired oven he built himself.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="timeline-item-wxy901">
                <div class="timeline-year-zab234">1995</div>
                <div class="timeline-content-cde567">
                    <h3>Family Expansion</h3>
                    <p>As word spread about Tony's incredible pizza, the business grew. His wife Maria joined the operation, bringing her own family recipes for fresh pasta and traditional Italian desserts. They expanded to include a full Italian menu while keeping pizza as their specialty.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="timeline-item-wxy901">
                <div class="timeline-year-zab234">2003</div>
                <div class="timeline-content-cde567">
                    <h3>Second Generation</h3>
                    <p>Tony's son Marco took over daily operations, introducing modern efficiency while preserving traditional methods. Under his leadership, the pizzeria became a cornerstone of the community, hosting local events and supporting neighborhood initiatives.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="timeline-item-wxy901">
                <div class="timeline-year-zab234">2018</div>
                <div class="timeline-content-cde567">
                    <h3>Modern Heritage</h3>
                    <p>Today, Tony's granddaughter Sofia represents the third generation, bringing fresh ideas while honoring the family legacy. The pizzeria now offers online ordering and delivery while maintaining the same commitment to quality and community that started it all.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

